.cs 3 on
.item 'SHOW AMESSAGE Command' 'Added on 03/16/81 by EAB'
.boxon
SHOW AMESSAGE [collect-options]
.*            <--------------->
.* FIELD COMMAND SHOW AMESSAGE collect-options
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SHOW AMESSAGE (or SHOW AMSG) command displays any accounting message that
appears in the SHOW CHARGES command response.  If there is no accounting
message when you issue a SHOW AMESSAGE command, WYLBUR displays the response,
"No accounting message.".

.* SELECT 'SHOW AMESSAGE Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION COLLECT-OPTIONS,BY,KEEP,NOCLEAR,NOCLR,CLEAR,CLR,WARN,NOWARN
.optix collect-options
collect-options\allow you to insert the system response to the SHOW AMESSAGE
                command into your active file.  Type HELP COLLECT-OPTIONS for
                a description of these options.
.cs 3 off
